DIV1.P:
But as force never yet could be effectual over Religi∣on;
so all these Proceedings serv'd but to make the
persecuted People encrease.

DIV2.P:
These drove them out of the Church, and these only;
for as to Doctrinal Articles, they are allow'd to be Or∣thodox,
and all the Dissenters frankly subscribe them,
the Quakers excepted, and the last Clause of the 27th.
Article to the Anabaptists.

The Word Union directs my Discourse, Union is the
Theme; and 'tis Peace in this Union I shall plead for;
however, you contemn the Man, listen to the Doctrine;
for let who will send the Teacher, the Teaching is from
Heaven.
